title: Risk of hydroxychloroquine alone and in combination with azithromycin in the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis: a multinational, retrospective study.
data_source: VA, DAGermany, IMRD AmbEMR, OpenClaims, CPRD, CCAE, MDCD, MDCR, IPCI, JMDC, Clinformatics, OptumEHR, SIDIAP
data_date: 01.09.2000 bis letztes verfügbares Datum 2020 in den Datenquellen
cohort_details:
Hydroxychloroquine, a drug commonly used in the 
treatment of rheumatoid arthritis, has received much negative publicity for adverse events associated with its authorisation for emergency use to treat patients with COVID-19 pneumonia. We studied the safety of hydroxychloroquine, alone and in combination with azithromycin, to determine the risk associated with its use in routine care in patients with rheumatoid arthritis.
med_details:
Hydroxychloroquine, 
sulfasalazine, Azithromycin, Amoxicillin ()RxNorm ingredient, ATC)
